<h3>How can i add button to the slider?</h3>
<div>
<p>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Fist of all you need to upload images for buttons into wordpress.</li>
<li>In "Main Slider Info" tab, in field "Apply Classes" describe selectors(example: classes) with background url properties of your buttons.
<br>
CSS Example ( .info_btn{ background:url("http://example.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/22/info.png") no-repeat; } ).
</li>
<li>Add in "Slider Items" tab new text items for your button with text or if you want without it (use "&amp;nbsp;").</li>
<li>In current text item section in field "Classes List" apply described earlier classes.</li>
<li>Use this item in your group.</li>
</ul>
All images used in such case not imported and exported.
</p>
</div>
<h3>How can i set background of text item transparent?</h3>
<div>
<p>
In field style of text item add : Example - background-color:rgba(55,55,55,0.1);
</p>
</div>
<h3>Can you show simple process of creating slider?</h3>
<div>
<p>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Fill main settings and save using tab "Slider Main Info".</li>
<li>Upload background images using tab "Slider Main Info".</li>
<li>Upload and setup all necessary image and texts items using tab "Slider Items".</li>
<li>Choose buttons and their top offset using tab "Slider Settings".</li>
<li>Create and setup containers, fill container's main settings, inner slider slides and single elements.
Setup start manipulation settings, move or delay points, and finish manipulation settings for each single element.</li>
<li>Get code from "Slider Paste Code" and paste it into some place.</li>
</ul>
</p>
